Resilience4j version: 2.1.0

Java version: 17

We have a Spring component, that looks something like this:
```java
public class RetryingClient {

    private final Client client;
    private final ApplicationEventPublisher applicationEventPublisher;

    public RetryingClient(Client client, ApplicationEventPublisher applicationEventPublisher) {
        this.client = client;
        this.applicationEventPublisher = applicationEventPublisher;
    }

    @Retry(name = "client", fallbackMethod = "onGetStatusFailed")
    public ClientStatus getStatus() {
        ClientStatus result = client.getStatus();
        applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new ConnectionEvent(Status.UP));
        return result;
    }

    private AimStatus onGetStatusFailed(RuntimeException e) {
        applicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(new ConnectionEvent(Status.DOWN));
        throw e;
    }
}
```

It stopped working in version `2.1.0` with the following error: `Cannot invoke "org.springframework.context.ApplicationEventPublisher.publishEvent(Object)" because "this.applicationEventPublisher" is null"` when retrying fails (executing the `onGetStatusFailed` method).

After debugging, it seems like that the issue is because of this change https://github.com/resilience4j/resilience4j/compare/v2.0.2...v2.1.0#diff-5c30a60f9a316effc456a031670dcc1ea32617a820fb1ce36c44aa1be2a521f2. It uses proxy with all fields null instead of the target with the correctly initialized fields.

